The paper deals with algorithmic and complexity issues related to graph problems, specifically the subgraph isomorphism problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The use of treewidth and circuit complexity also suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of graph parameters and lower bounds suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible sub-category.
